data.description: MOVE-IN READY!!! Welcome to this 3BR/2BA 2-story custom-built home that is located on CUL-DE-SAC in a gated community of OYSTER BAYOU. As you approach the property, the beautiful mature landscaping with palm trees and green grass sets the stage for what's to come. Use the stairs to walk up to the covered front porch that warps around the house and provides an ample space for outdoor relaxation. Enter through the double French doors and be captivated by vaulted ceilings, arched doorways, and engineered hardwood flooring designed to create a seamless flow throughout the home. The convenience of central vacuum cleaner that effortlessly reaches every corner of every room. Prepare to be dazzled by the chef's dream kitchen, meticulously crafted with the finest details in mind. Stainless steel appliances, a generous island boasting a built-in microwave, and an abundance of cabinet space await the culinary enthusiast. Experience the joy of cooking with a 6-burner gas stove and a stainless steel hood, while the custom-built rotating pantry with organizers is optimizing storage efficiency. Recessed lighting and contemporary fixtures hanging over the island create a warm and inviting ambiance, perfectly complementing the pristine quartz countertops. The kitchen and dining area has been masterfully remodeled to include hurricane windows and sliding glass doors. As you walk through those doors onto the wooden deck, you are welcomed with breathtaking views of trees and the wooded area. You can retreat to the spacious master bedroom featuring 2 spacious walk-in closets, and built in shelves. The en-suite bathroom comes with a large jetted bathtub, a walk-in shower, a private WC, and a double vanity with a makeup area. Bedroom #2 features a soaring high ceiling and an octagonal copula with eight windows and a ceiling fan where natural light floods through. On the other side of the house, adjacent to bedroom 3, is another bathroom designed with a decorative custom slate tile floor, wall, and countertop. This bathroom comes with a tub/shower combo and toilet/bidet. The laundry room is equipped with a washer, a dryer, and storage cabinets. The downstairs area accommodates two separate garages, one including a workshop in the back, providing the perfect space for pursuing creative projects or hobbies. Between the two garages, an extra room awaits, offering additional storage options. You will also find 2 sets of sliding glass doors, effortlessly blending indoor and outdoor living, allowing an easy access to the pool area. A beautiful custom-built stamped concrete decking surrounds the luxurious screened-in saltwater pool that is heated by solar panels. This beautiful home is located in the gated community that offers a private boat ramp to Oyster Bayou and easy access to the Gulf. Only minutes away from Robert Rees Memorial Park, 45-acre beachfront with 650-foot boardwalk, observation tower, and picnicking areas. Fishing, canoe and kayak access. The quaint town of New Port Richey is about 2 miles away offering small business shopping, dining and entertainment, plus large public library. There is also a beautiful park with walking trail, pet friendly, and boat launch. Tampa International Airport is 45 minutes away. Florida living at its best! No flooding or water damage from the hurricane, so schedule your showing today!
